60g breadcrumbs 178cals
420g spiral or other short pasta 1538cals
3 tbsp/42g unsalted butter 313cals
2 garlic cloves 
1.5 tsp mustard
4.5tbsp/45g plain flour 154cals
750ml whole milk 
375g extra mature cheddar 1474cals
37g parmesan for sauce 149cals
25g Parmesan for topping 100cals
10 turns of salt
30 turns of pepper 

Put oven on to 180C. Cook pasta for 2 mins less than the stated time then drain well. Melt the butter in a pan. Add the garlic and cook for 1 min, then stir in the plain flour. Cook for 1 min more, then gradually whisk in the milk until you have a lump-free sauce. Bring to a simmer and continue to simmer for 5 mins, whisking all the time until thickened. Take off the heat, then stir in the cheddar, mustard and half the parmesan. Stir in the pasta and some seasoning into the cheesy sauce. Tip into a large ovenproof dish. Scatter over the breadcrumbs and the remaining parmesan, then bake for 35 mins until crisp and golden. Can be frozen before baking – defrost thoroughly before cooking.

Serves 4. 977cals / person. 

Can be used for Cauliflower Cheese too. Just cut the cauliflower into chunks and boil for 5 mins in place of the pasta. 

Ingredients for 2

30g breadcrumbs (22g)
210g spiral or other short pasta (153g)
1.5 tbsp/21g unsalted butter (1tbsp/15g)
1 garlic cloves 
0.75 tsp mustard (0.5 tsp)
2.25tbsp/22.5g plain flour (1.6tbsp/16g)
375ml whole milk (273ml)
187.5g extra mature cheddar (136g)
18.5g parmesan for sauce (14g)
12.5g Parmesan for topping (9g)
5 turns of salt (3)
15 turns of pepper (8)

977 cals (710 cals) per person.
